# Delgoosh — Cursor AI Rules
# These rules apply to every file in this project.

## Project overview
Delgoosh is a Persian/English online psychotherapy platform.
It has two apps: patient and therapist, sharing one design system.

## Architecture rules

### Imports
- ALWAYS import UI primitives from `@ds` (the design system barrel)
- NEVER import from deep paths like `@ds/primitives` or `../../design-system/tokens`
- Asset imports use `@assets/...`
- Screen-to-screen imports are FORBIDDEN — screens are isolated

### Language & direction
- NEVER hardcode `direction: 'rtl'` or any font-family directly in screen files
- ALWAYS get `dir` from `useLang()` and pass it to the root element
- ALWAYS inject CSS with `<style>{makeGlobalCSS(lang)}</style>` at the top of each screen
- Use `layoutFor(dir)` helpers for all directional margins, paddings, and borders
- NEVER use `marginLeft/Right` directly — use `L.marginStart(n)` / `L.marginEnd(n)`

### Strings & numbers
- NEVER hardcode UI strings in JSX — always use `t('key.subkey')` from `useLang()`
- NEVER render raw numbers in UI — always use `n(number)` for locale-aware numerals
- Add new strings to BOTH `fa.js` and `en.js` simultaneously

### Responsive layout
- Use `useIsDesktop()` to branch between desktop (sidebar) and mobile (bottom-nav) layouts
- Desktop threshold: 900px
- Desktop: fixed 230px sidebar, `.ds-sidebar` + `.ds-main` classes
- Mobile: bottom nav with max 5 items, `.ds-bottom-nav` class

### Styling
- Inline styles only — no CSS modules, no Tailwind, no styled-components
- Use `COLORS.*` tokens for all color values
- Use `RADIUS.*` for border-radius
- Use `SHADOW.*` for box-shadow
- Use `SPACING.*` for consistent spacing values
- Animation: use class names like `.ds-anim-fadeUp`, `.ds-stagger` from the global CSS

### Component patterns
- `Button` variant prop: 'primary' | 'accent' | 'ghost' | 'ghost2' | 'danger' | 'warn'
- `Button` size prop: 'md' | 'sm' | 'xs'
- `Tag` color prop: 'primary' | 'success' | 'warn' | 'danger' | 'accent' | 'neutral'
- `Card` variant prop: 'default' | 'sm' | 'ghost' | 'tinted'
- `Modal` — always include onClose, title, children; wide=true for 680px max
- Session cards use `.ds-session-card` class (teal gradient, already defined in CSS)

### File size discipline
- Each screen file should stay under 300 lines
- If a screen grows beyond 300 lines, extract sub-components into a co-located folder:
  e.g. `screens/Dashboard/` with `SessionCard.jsx`, `CancelModal.jsx`, etc.
- The screen's `index.jsx` then imports from its own sub-components

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT use localStorage or sessionStorage in screen components (use Context)
- Do NOT add new icons to icons.jsx without documenting in this file
- Do NOT use emoji as UI elements — use Ic components
- Do NOT use `<form>` tags — use button onClick handlers
- Do NOT use any CSS framework (Tailwind, Bootstrap, etc.)

